cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the dynamics of information cascades in social networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes a framework for predicting cascade dynamics. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it uses social network data for its experiments. The paper also involves data-driven learning and classification, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) respectively.
